{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011BudZB2Y2EXGuSrfVRitCg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n     2â†’\n     3â†’#[error_code]\n     4â†’pub enum CoinflipError {\n     5â†’    /// 6100 (Anchor adds 6000 base offset)\n     6â†’    #[msg(\"Invalid side: must be 0 (Heads) or 1 (Tails)\")]\n     7â†’    InvalidSide = 100,\n     8â†’\n     9â†’    /// 6101\n    10â†’    #[msg(\"Invalid tier index\")]\n    11â†’    InvalidTier,\n    12â†’\n    13â†’    /// 6102\n    14â†’    #[msg(\"Match is not in the expected phase\")]\n    15â†’    InvalidPhase,\n    16â†’\n    17â†’    /// 6103\n    18â†’    #[msg(\"Insufficient funds for entry amount\")]\n    19â†’    InsufficientFunds,\n    20â†’\n    21â†’    /// 6104\n    22â†’    #[msg(\"Creator cannot join their own match\")]\n    23â†’    CannotJoinOwnMatch,\n    24â†’\n    25â†’    /// 6105\n    26â†’    #[msg(\"Only the oracle authority can resolve matches\")]\n    27â†’    UnauthorizedOracle,\n    28â†’\n    29â†’    /// 6106\n    30â†’    #[msg(\"Payout has already been claimed\")]\n    31â†’    AlreadyClaimed,\n    32â†’\n    33â†’    /// 6107\n    34â†’    #[msg(\"Only the winner can claim the payout\")]\n    35â†’    NotWinner,\n    36â†’\n    37â†’    /// 6108\n    38â†’    #[msg(\"Match can only be cancelled in WAITING phase\")]\n    39â†’    CannotCancel,\n    40â†’\n    41â†’    /// 6109\n    42â†’    #[msg(\"VRF randomness request failed\")]\n    43â†’    VrfRequestFailed,\n    44â†’\n    45â†’    /// 6110\n    46â†’    #[msg(\"Lock timeout has not elapsed yet\")]\n    47â†’    LockTimeoutNotElapsed,\n    48â†’\n    49â†’    /// 6111\n    50â†’    #[msg(\"Only the creator or opponent can cancel a timed-out match\")]\n    51â†’    UnauthorizedCaller,\n    52â†’}\n    53â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ls6eE1rz4QYaFd3aFc4AJz","session_id":"3ef31b5a-f057-490b-97be-2b7d8a2c562f","uuid":"a4630844-a6c6-41cd-8694-85359319b906"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ls6eE1rz4QYaFd3aFc4AJz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## Exploration Complete: Lamport Transfer Patterns\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase and identified all lamport transfer patterns used across the Coinflip program and shared library. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n---\n\n### **Pattern Overview**\n\nThe codebase uses **two distinct lamport transfer approaches**:\n\n#### **Pattern 1: Direct Lamport Manipulation (via `try_borrow_mut_lamports`)**\nUsed for transferring lamports between accounts already held in the Accounts struct.\n\n**Examples:**\n- **claim_payout.rs** (lines 104-110):\n  ```rust\n  let match_info = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info();\n  **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= payout;\n  **ctx.accounts.winner.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += payout;\n  \n  **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= fee;\n  **ctx.accounts.treasury.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += fee;\n  ```\n\n- **timeout_cancel.rs** (lines 63-68): Two refunds from escrow\n  ```rust\n  let match_info = ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info();\n  **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= entry_amount;\n  **ctx.accounts.creator.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += entry_amount;\n  \n  **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= entry_amount;\n  **ctx.accounts.opponent.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += entry_amount;\n  ```\n\n- **force_close.rs** (lines 37-39): Drain all lamports\n  ```rust\n  let lamports = match_info.lamports();\n  **match_info.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? -= lamports;\n  **ctx.accounts.recipient.try_borrow_mut_lamports()? += lamports;\n  ```\n\n#### **Pattern 2: CPI Transfer via System Program**\nUsed for depositing initial funds from a signer into an escrow account.\n\n**Examples:**\n- **create_match.rs** (lines 34-43):\n  ```rust\n  system_program::transfer(\n      CpiContext::new(\n          ctx.accounts.system_program.to_account_info(),\n          system_program::Transfer {\n              from: ctx.accounts.creator.to_account_info(),\n              to: ctx.accounts.coinflip_match.to_account_info(),\n          },\n      ),\n      entry_amount,\n  )?;\n  ```\n\n- **join_match.rs** (lines 70-79): Identical pattern for opponent joining\n\n---\n\n### **Key Characteristics**\n\n| Aspect | Direct Manipulation | CPI Transfer |\n|--------|-------------------|--------------|\n| **Use Case** | PDA-to-recipient, PDA-to-PDA transfers | Signer-to-PDA deposits |\n| **Method** | `try_borrow_mut_lamports()` | `system_program::transfer()` CPI |\n| **Account Ownership** | Works across any account owned by program | Requires system program for signing |\n| **Error Handling** | Returns `Result<()>` from `try_borrow_mut_lamports()?` | Returns `Result<()>` from CPI call |\n| **Advantage** | No CPI overhead, simpler for same-program transfers | Standard Solana pattern, cleaner semantics |\n\n---\n\n### **Current Shared Library Structure**\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/shared/`\n\n**Cargo.toml dependencies:**\n```toml\nanchor-lang = { workspace = true }\nsolana-sha256-hasher = { workspace = true }\n```\n\n**Current modules in lib.rs:**\n- `commit_reveal`\n- `constants`\n- `fees`\n- `lifecycle`\n- `pause`\n- `tiers`\n- `timeout`\n\n**Existing patterns observed:**\n- Small, focused utility modules\n- Tests included in each module\n- Simple public functions (no Result returns typically)\n- Pure computation functions (fees, tier amounts, phase validation)\n\n---\n\n### **For the escrow.rs Module**\n\nBased on the exploration, `escrow.rs` should:\n\n1. **Provide two main helper functions:**\n   - `transfer_from_escrow()` - for PDA-to-recipient transfers (direct manipulation)\n   - `refund_to_account()` - for refunding participants (direct manipulation)\n\n2. **Use the direct lamport manipulation pattern** since it will operate on accounts already held in Accounts structs\n\n3. **Include Result returns** to propagate `try_borrow_mut_lamports()` errors\n\n4. **Match the existing shared module style:**\n   - Focused scope\n   - Comprehensive tests\n   - No external error types needed (errors come from `try_borrow_mut_lamports()`)\n   - Documentation comments for each function\n\n5. **Parameters should be:** `&AccountInfo`, amounts as `u64`, and return `Result<()>`\n\n---\n\n### **File Content Summary**\n\n| File | Key Pattern |\n|------|------------|\n| claim_payout.rs | Payout from PDA to winner + fee to treasury (direct manipulation) |\n| create_match.rs | Initial deposit CPI (system_program::transfer) |\n| join_match.rs | Initial deposit CPI (system_program::transfer) |\n| cancel_match.rs | Implicit via `close = creator` (Anchor auto-refunds rent) |\n| timeout_cancel.rs | Two refunds from PDA (direct manipulation, sequential) |\n| force_close.rs | Drain all lamports from broken account (direct manipulation) |\n| resolve_match.rs | No transfers; only state updates |\n\nThe shared library already has 7 modules and no error codesâ€”escrow.rs should follow the same lightweight, utility-focused pattern with pure transfer helpers and comprehensive tests."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac275a01cd45fa867 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 43333\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 35681</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ef31b5a-f057-490b-97be-2b7d8a2c562f","uuid":"2a7609c2-b128-426c-9b1c-2b5308de330a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to create `solana/shared/src/escrow.rs` with lamport transfer helpers. Explore the following areas thoroughly:\n\n1. **Coinflip claim_payout.rs** - Look at `sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/claim_payout.rs` for the existing PDA-to-recipient lamport transfer pattern (using `try_borrow_mut_lamports`)\n2. **Coinflip create_match.rs** - Look at